Test suite for the runner module, covering the five entry points: `migrate` (one-time seed from markdown), `add_task`, `delete_task`, `list`, and `render`.

Uses `FakeFs`, an in-memory `Fs` implementation backed by `BTreeMap<String, String>`, so tests don't touch the real filesystem. The store is a JSON array of tasks persisted to `paths.store`; `list` and `render` deserialize it directly (no backfilling), while `migrate`, `add_task`, and `delete_task` each read, mutate, and re-serialize it.

Key invariants being tested: `migrate` seeds the store from a markdown table, assigns sequential ids in source order, and refuses to run twice. `add_task` appends without reordering the store, assigns a fresh id past the current max, and rejects invalid impact values. `delete_task` removes a row by id, keeps the rest in insertion order, and errors on unknown ids. `render` re-syncs the markdown view from a hand-edited store without mutating the store. `list` (tested indirectly) backfills missing ids for legacy rows, assigning them in store order even though tasks display in priority order (high/easy before low/hard).

The `stored()` helper deserializes raw JSON without backfilling, so tests see exactly what was persisted — this is load-bearing for verifying store mutation.